    http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/finance/v3

    ValueWithAttributes Voucher

      • http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/finance/v3:Voucher

      • Description

        A form of payment using a voucher or coupon.

    • Example XML

      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>

<Voucher billingNumber="234872648" effectiveDate="1999-07-16" electronicIndicatorInd="true" expireDate="2022-07-16" expireDateExclusiveInd="true" groupDaysApplyInd="true" identifier="voucher_1" organization="Acme" seriesCode="87462746283" supplierIdentifier="6473243874" system="sysABC3344" url="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" valueType="Full" xmlns="http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/finance/v3"/>

      • Attribute Summary

        Attributes 
        Name Description
        seriesCode
        Identification of a series of coupons or vouchers identified by serial number(s).
        Details
        Type StringTiny
        Example Value 87462746283
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        effectiveDate
        Indicates the starting date.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:date
        Example Value 1999-07-16
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        expireDate
        Indicates the ending date.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:date
        Example Value 2022-07-16
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        billingNumber
        Reference of the billing account which handles the payment transaction.
        Details
        Type StringShort
        Example Value 234872648
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        supplierIdentifier
        Unique identifier of the electronic voucher, created by the supplier.
        Details
        Type Identifier
        Example Value 6473243874
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        identifier
        Unique identifier of the electronic voucher.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:ID
        Example Value voucher_1
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        valueType
        Defines the type of voucher (e.g., full credit or partial credit).
        Details
        Type StringTiny
        Example Value Full
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1

      • Indicator Summary

        Indicators 
        Name Description
        groupDaysApplyInd
        When true, specifies the Group Days Apply Value can be used for this Voucher Billing Account. This indicator is used to allow the usage of a car rental days voucher when part of an inclusive tour.
        electronicIndicatorInd
        When true, indicates the voucher is electronic. An E-voucher is a value document issued by the Travel Agent for the customer. The e-voucher can be used as a proof of reservation, but more normally, as a full-payment or partial payment.
        expireDateExclusiveInd
        When true, indicates that the ExpireDate is the first day after the applicable period (e.g. when expire date is Oct 15 the last date of the period is Oct 14).
